<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-376D0A1C-9879-4E95-B0A8-FF888B737E51" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-376D0A1C-9879-4E95-B0A8-FF888B737E51" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Send the replaced printhead back </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-4AD32E82-3B09-4750-B121-7BFEC572A15E"><p class="- topic/p ">Return the replaced printhead to Venlo. Aim: to be able to analyze printheads. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To be able to shorten the feedback loop of failed printheads the replaced printheads should be sent for analyses to Venlo as soon as possible. This is done by a special transport procedure to decrease the time of transport over the world and an "urgent"-sticker to speed up the internal processes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The return includes 4 steps: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Packing of the printhead. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Enter information in ADAM. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Add an Urgent sticker. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Prepare for shipping. 
</p></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-81A864A3-C7D1-4BCC-ADD8-6083F88DB485" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/></section><section id="SECTION_4B6D6D9F64084A75831EB5ABF7C5493D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Packing of the printhead</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_3863BC2306F646DB8526178EBC27A2A4" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fill out the sticker (on the blister) with the required information. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-65E3AC11-CDDA-4DB3-BED2-610D5FF9D7E9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E729BA6E-5F05-4205-B58D-60D7652AC883-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E729BA6E-5F05-4205-B58D-60D7652AC883-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If a black rubber band is present in the package of the new printhead, place this rubber band as shown in the picture. Otherwise just put the green cap over the printhead. 
</p><note id="GUID-05E5C2C9-91E3-41CF-BCC2-B723F1BCDD20" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This is to prevent ink leakage from the nozzles during transport 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-35AC3074-E034-4F92-AAAC-A72C2E020DB7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E0A388A5-25BF-4EAE-B478-911AB9F59C99-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E0A388A5-25BF-4EAE-B478-911AB9F59C99-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the blister in the bag of the printhead: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">1. Fold the top part of the bag over the printhead with a blister. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">2. Seal the bag with normal tape (over the total width). 
</p><note id="GUID-8A811081-2596-4E78-8949-DD2EE88EACF9" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This is to prevent ink leakage during transport. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E95A9E8D-38BC-405F-89D3-9931A93ECB60" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C000ADF1-E67E-4C52-8C8C-A2FEA5B1D07F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C000ADF1-E67E-4C52-8C8C-A2FEA5B1D07F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Do the Printhead quality check again. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-4FCBBAC0-BC24-4289-8F8A-0776A209596F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2BA40A55-045A-41BA-8A55-30654DED507E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2BA40A55-045A-41BA-8A55-30654DED507E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Put the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">2</b> Printhead quality check prints in the box as well. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Send the failing parts back to CPP 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref keyref="How_to_send_failing_parts" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-43285AC7-EDFF-42E6-A29B-7033DEEA1291.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to send (failing) parts back to CPP and apply for a warranty?>How to send (failing) parts back to CPP and apply for a warranty</xref> 
